            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I try to repro and fix it, but because i dont understand the lua stuff it wasn't easy to write an acceptable functional test for it, even with ai assist, so i don't open a PR, but i do have a patch that seem work on my device. so i think i can share it here.\n\nadd a global var `initaldir` and store the directory at `main.c` and pass it in `src/nvim/ex_docmd.c:ex_restart`\n```\nChannel *channel = channel_job_start(argv, exepath,\n                                       CALLBACK_READER_INIT, on_err, CALLBACK_NONE,\n                                       false, true, true, detach, kChannelStdinPipe,\n                                       initialdir, 0, 0, NULL, &exit_status);\n```\n\nTo drop the `[files]` in `ex_restart()`\n```\nbool keep_next = false;  // Mark next arg as an option value, keep it.\n  TV_LIST_ITER_CONST(l, li,{\n...\n// Long options that take a value\n    if (i > 0\n        && (strequal(arg, \"--cmd\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"--server\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"--startuptime\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"--listen\"))) {\n      argv[i++] = xstrdup(arg);\n      keep_next = true;\n      continue;\n    }\n    // Short options that take a value\n    if (i > 0\n        && (strequal(arg, \"-u\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"-c\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"-S\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"-i\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"-t\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"-q\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"-w\")\n            || strequal(arg, \"-W\"))) {\n      argv[i++] = xstrdup(arg);\n      keep_next = true;\n      continue;\n    }\n...\n}\n```\n\ni also have a simple repro.lua that print the log, and the content in log seem ok to me\n\n[repro_restart.lua.gz](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/27303195/repro_restart.lua.gz)\n",
