            "body": "I got your concern, if there's new options need value next to it, we have to modify twice in my case. To leverage `command_line_scan`, the same logical we share is that we want to mark the options need next value,\n\nso maybe extract  `bool is_opt_with_value(const char*)`, inside is a `switch case` or `char*[]`, and let it be the only truth. Once we wanna add new argument just add it here.  Replace the `want_argument = true` with it, and some adjust about `argv_idx=xxx`",
